notes: The Debut Race is mandatory for every character, and takes place in the second half of June of the first year.
There are several different types of the Debut Race (varying in length and surface), and which one you get depends on the character trained.
If you don't win the Debut, you're gonna have to win any Maiden Race before participating in any standard races.
Maiden Races will start showing up one turn after the Debut Race, if you didn't place 1st in it.
There will be multiple of them available every turn, and will keep showing up until you win at least one of them.
You can't participate in any races listed here until you win either Debut or any of the Maiden Races.

Fun fact: Haru Urara can technically go the entire first half of her training without winning a single race, and for that reason, there are Maiden Races scheduled all the way until August of the second year.
